Privacy Policy
Last Updated: October 2, 2024
Welcome to the Surfline\Wavetrak group privacy policy.
Surfline\Wavetrak, Inc. is a corporation registered in Delaware, United States of America. The group of companies operating under the “Surfline” brand (and to whom this policy applies) is made up of different legal entities including, Surfline\Wavetrak, Inc., Wavetrak Limited, Wavetrak Oceania Pty Ltd, and Surfline NZ Limited (collectively, “Surfline”). This Privacy Policy is issued on behalf of the Surfline group of companies so when we mention "Surfline", "we", "us" or "our" in this Privacy Policy, we are referring to the relevant company in the Surfline group of companies responsible for processing your data.
We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy will inform you as to how we look after your personal data in connection with your access to or use of our websites, apps, products and services (including without limitation Surfline’s domains and subdomains, cameras, forecasts, Cam Rewind, Surfline Sessions, and Perks) (collectively, the “Services”). It also tells you about your privacy rights and how the law protects you.
Please also read our
Terms of Use
for more information on the terms governing the Services.
If you are a resident of the United States of America, United Kingdom or European Economic Area, please refer to the separate annexes which provide further details relevant to those jurisdictions and outline any further rights you may have under this policy.
